I want to give us three.

38:31.906 --> 38:35.430
three things to take away, then I want us to spend some time praying.

38:37.652 --> 38:39.594
How do we help each other sing our pain in the presence of God?

38:39.614 --> 38:40.355
Number one, listen.

38:42.538 --> 38:42.858
Listen.

38:44.380 --> 38:49.345
It's possible to be a people who know all the answers before we've even heard the questions.

38:51.708 --> 38:54.891
And in that way, we become like Job's friends, right?

38:55.512 --> 39:01.298
Quick to the trigger, quick with the truth, quick of the solution, quick with the answer,

39:01.474 --> 39:02.876
Quick to be edgy and prophetic.

39:05.198 --> 39:06.540
We need to patiently listen.

39:07.261 --> 39:09.604
And that leads to number two, with that empathize.

39:10.825 --> 39:13.689
Listen and empathize.

39:13.769 --> 39:17.133
Don't invalidate people's pain.

39:19.015 --> 39:20.177
Don't invalidate people's pain.

39:20.217 --> 39:23.661
Look, no amount of good theology can take the pain out of suffering.

39:25.683 --> 39:27.866
No amount of good theology can take the pain out of suffering.

39:27.906 --> 39:31.410
Just believing that, that truth alone should make the church more gentle.

39:32.610 --> 39:36.737
should make us more forbearing and patient with our brothers and sisters who are in pain.

39:36.817 --> 39:38.359
And let me just say this while we're here.

39:38.660 --> 39:40.182
We need to be less shockable.

39:41.885 --> 39:42.346
Put it that way.

39:43.347 --> 39:44.970
Less prone to being shocked.

39:45.190 --> 39:52.221
No one in the world should be less shocked by all the hard things and the bad things we experience in sin and in suffering than Christians.

39:53.223 --> 39:53.423
Why?

39:53.664 --> 39:57.650
Because we have Bibles and we've read Genesis 3.

39:58.370 --> 40:03.939
And we see the fingerprints of Genesis 3 over everything that follows Genesis 3.

40:04.059 --> 40:06.543
The world is wall-papered in Genesis 3.

40:06.663 --> 40:07.464
And we know it well.

40:07.564 --> 40:08.826
Nobody should know it better than we do.

40:09.327 --> 40:15.036
Nobody should be less shocked, less prone for our eyebrows to jump off our foreheads when we hear, oh my goodness.

40:15.056 --> 40:15.596
You said, what?

40:16.518 --> 40:17.299
We shouldn't be shocked.

40:18.461 --> 40:21.445
We should see this coming because we had a book to tell us.

40:22.427 --> 40:24.530
And we should be hope dealers in the world.

40:25.826 --> 40:29.532
right here in the middle of the chaos and the funk that is this world.

40:29.572 --> 40:32.116
We should be right here dealing hope.

40:35.361 --> 40:45.137
Earlier this year, our friend Ray Orland, who spoke here last year, he said this, churches for all the soldiers who can't fight anymore.

40:46.339 --> 40:49.203
They've given and given to the point of exhaustion.

40:49.985 --> 40:50.866
If that's you,

40:50.978 --> 40:53.601
In coming to a manual, that's the name of the church.

40:53.621 --> 40:55.903
In coming to a manual, you don't have to be up.

40:56.423 --> 40:57.384
You don't have to serve.

40:57.724 --> 40:58.926
You don't have to smile.

40:59.226 --> 41:03.390
You can just sit there, breathe, and quietly heal.

41:04.191 --> 41:07.033
The Lord Himself will take care for you.

41:08.875 --> 41:10.036
I don't just like that.

41:10.437 --> 41:12.479
I love that.

41:13.600 --> 41:20.146
That's what we need to be as a church, a haven, refuge-like, a fortress.

41:20.386 --> 41:26.954
fighting with people, comrades in the fight of faith, patient with sufferers.

41:27.534 --> 41:28.936
And third, pray.

41:32.560 --> 41:38.327
Studying through a book filled with prayers, it shouldn't surprise us that two weeks in a row, one of the application points is to pray.

41:40.229 --> 41:45.195
And I'm actually even gonna invite the worship team if they would come out and join me here.

41:45.255 --> 41:47.538
I'm gonna lead us in a time of prayer in just a moment.

41:48.418 --> 41:50.020
for those who are walking through trials.

41:50.040 --> 41:53.104
So don't check out, actually lean in here.

41:56.548 --> 42:00.533
I want to invite us to do something we hardly ever do, but I'm not apologizing for it.

42:00.713 --> 42:10.706
I think we need to spend some time praying for one another and even inviting those who are suffering deeply to come forward.

42:11.554 --> 42:14.659
and to be prayed for by friends and brothers and sisters.

42:14.799 --> 42:20.007
And I'm gonna offer some categories in just a moment for some things, but you might already know, it's me, it's me.

42:20.729 --> 42:22.151
This message has been all over me.

42:23.072 --> 42:25.797
I'm desperate, I need God, and so I'm coming.

42:25.857 --> 42:28.541
And so if that's you, by all means, you can start coming now.

42:31.466 --> 42:39.378
You know, it's, this is a sweet observation, I think, tucked in the end of Jesus' life.

42:41.506 --> 42:42.747
So he's in the Garden of Gethsemane.

42:44.109 --> 42:45.470
He's tripping over himself.

42:45.610 --> 42:47.712
It says he's repeatedly falling down.

42:49.053 --> 42:50.715
He has lost his strength.

42:51.396 --> 42:52.657
He is God forsaken.

42:53.197 --> 42:54.679
Heaven is utterly silent.

42:55.600 --> 42:56.240
And what does he want?

42:56.340 --> 42:59.303
What does the Savior of the world want in the last moments of his life?

42:59.323 --> 43:00.504
He's sweating drops of blood.

43:00.524 --> 43:01.085
He's anxious.

43:02.767 --> 43:05.629
And he looks around and he says, will you watch with me?

43:09.453 --> 43:10.354
He wants friends.

43:12.066 --> 43:20.850
He wants disciples not sleeping over there, but with their hands on his back, the Savior of the world wants his friends watching with him in prayer.

